                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.001 Montero, Juan/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-27T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 27, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Reference Embassy’s despatch No. 1013, November 5, 1931. At the time of the
                    inauguration of President Montero, you may extend to <pb facs="1033" n="919"
                        xml:id="pg_919"/> him the cordial congratulations of the President and the
                    assurances of his best wishes for the success of Señor Montero’s
                    administration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
